<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Boivin's collection number 2658 was applied to several different collection events. 
<bibRefCitation author="Baillon, H" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="139 - 173" refId="B3" refString="Baillon, H, 1861. Euphorbiacees Africaines. Deuxieme Partie, Afrique Orientale (Bourbon, Maurice, Madagascar, Zanguebar, etc.). Adansonia 1: 139 - 173" title="Euphorbiacees Africaines. Deuxieme Partie, Afrique Orientale (Bourbon, Maurice, Madagascar, Zanguebar, etc.)." volume="1" year="1861">Baillon (1861)</bibRefCitation>
was apparently aware of this given the greater detail in which he cited Boivin's specimens, such as &quot;Boivin (1848), n. 2658, Madag., baie de Rigny (h. Mus.)&quot; under 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton brevispicatus" order="Malpighiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevispicatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Croton brevispicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and &quot;Boivin, n. 2658, cap 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Ambre”">d'Ambre&quot;</normalizedToken>
under 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. squamiger" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="squamiger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. squamiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Baill. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mueller, J" editor="Candolle, AP de" journalOrPublisher="Paris, Strasbourg, &amp; London" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="189 - 1261" refId="B51" refString="Mueller, J, 1866. Euphorbiaceae. In: Candolle, AP de, Ed., Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 15(2). Paris, Strasbourg, &amp; London: 189 - 1261" title="Euphorbiaceae." volumeTitle="Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 15 (2)." year="1866">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
(1866)
</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. brevispicatus" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="brevispicatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. brevispicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Baill., as well as the type of that species (&quot;Boivin n. 2658! in hb. Mus. Paris&quot;), in his treatment of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. brachybotryus" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="brachybotryus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. brachybotryus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which we interpret as an illegitimate name for 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. brevispicatus" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="brevispicatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. brevispicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The isotype at P was a gift from the Caen herbarium received by the Paris herbarium in 1974, and it was never annotated by Baillon, although it had been annotated by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
